American Football fans are counting down to the start of Super Bowl LVI, which sees the L.A. Rams tackle the Cincinnati Bengals at the SoFi Stadium in Inglewood. With the game starting at 11.30pm GMT in the UK, it's going to be a late night for anybody planning to stay up and watch the action unfold live. If you want to keep yourself entertained (and awake) in the build up to the big game, Express Online has put together a special Super Bowl Sunday gaming quiz for fans of the popular sport. Featuring eight tricky questions, your job is to identify the American Football game based on an image and a clue. Check out the quiz below and let us know how you get on. Congratulations if you managed to get every question right, except for the first one, that was easy. If you're looking for some virtual NFL action in the run up to the event, your best bet is NFL 22. The game features lots of new and improved features, including changes to the Franchise mode. "All-new features in Franchise include staff management, an enhanced scenario engine, and weekly strategy. Share avatar progress and player class between Face of The Franchise and The Yard with unified progression. And for the first time ever in Ultimate Team, adjust Superstar X-Factors at halftime." As for today's game, you'd have been hard pressed to find anyone predicting a Bengals vs Rams final at the start of the season. Just two years after finishing with the worst league in the record, the Cincinnati Bengals will be playing their first Super Bowl in 33 years. The Rams, meanwhile, were last in the Super Bowl just four years ago when they lost to the New England Patriots at Super Bowl 2018. The Rams do have one Super Bowl title to their name, and as fate will have it are playing at their home ground this weekend.